# NestJS + TypeORM Backend Monorepo вЂ” Implementation Plan

Build a **NestJS backend** with **TypeORM** (PostgreSQL) inside a monorepo alongside the existing React/Vite frontend.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database connection**: You'll need a PostgreSQL instance running locally or remotely. The plan assumes `localhost:5432` with a database called `kr_fuels`. Please confirm or provide your connection details.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Moving frontend files**: The existing root-level frontend code will be moved into `apps/frontend/`. Git history is preserved since it's a move, not a delete. Is this acceptable?

---

