### Frontend Migration

Move all current frontend source files into `apps/frontend/`:
- [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/App.tsx), [index.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/index.tsx), [index.html](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/index.html), [types.ts](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts), [utils.ts](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/utils.ts)
- `components/`, `pages/`
- [vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/vite.config.ts), [tsconfig.json](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/tsconfig.json), [package.json](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/package.json)

The frontend [package.json](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/package.json) keeps its existing dependencies unchanged. Vite dev server still runs on port `5173`.

---

### NestJS Backend вЂ” `apps/backend/`

#### [NEW] [package.json](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/apps/backend/package.json)
NestJS dependencies:
- `@nestjs/core`, `@nestjs/common`, `@nestjs/platform-express`
- `@nestjs/typeorm`, `typeorm`, `pg`
- `@nestjs/jwt`, `@nestjs/passport`, `passport`, `passport-jwt`, `bcrypt`
- `@nestjs/config`, `class-validator`, `class-transformer`

#### [NEW] [main.ts](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/apps/backend/src/main.ts)
Bootstrap NestJS on port `3000` with global validation pipe, CORS enabled for frontend origin.

#### [NEW] [app.module.ts](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/apps/backend/src/app.module.ts)
Root module importing `TypeOrmModule.forRootAsync()`, `ConfigModule`, and all feature modules.

#### [NEW] [database.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/apps/backend/src/config/database.config.ts)
TypeORM config reading from `.env`: host, port, username, password, database. `synchronize: true` for development.

---

### TypeORM Entities

Maps directly to the [database_schema.md](file:///C:/Users/Srivarmaa/.gemini/antigravity/brain/1b55b29f-b5cc-43b9-8673-40c1da4cbfe0/database_schema.md) we already designed.

| Entity | Key Relations |
|---|---|
| [Bunk](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#2-8) | `OneToMany в†’ Account`, `OneToMany в†’ Voucher`, `ManyToMany в†’ User` |
| [User](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#9-16) | `ManyToMany в†’ Bunk` (via join table), role enum |
| [Account](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#17-26) | `ManyToOne в†’ self` (parent), `ManyToOne в†’ Bunk`, `OneToMany в†’ Voucher` |
| [Voucher](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#27-37) | `ManyToOne в†’ Account`, `ManyToOne в†’ Bunk` |
| [Reminder](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#47-56) | `createdBy` в†’ username string (loose relation) |

---

### API Modules & Endpoints

#### Auth Module
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/auth/login` | Login with username + password в†’ JWT token |
| `GET` | `/auth/profile` | Get current user (from JWT) |

- JWT strategy with `@nestjs/passport`
- `RolesGuard` decorator: `@Roles('super_admin')` for admin-only routes
- Passwords hashed with **bcrypt**

#### Bunks Module
| Method | Endpoint | Auth |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/bunks` | All users (filtered by access) |
| `POST` | `/bunks` | `super_admin` only |
| `DELETE` | `/bunks/:id` | `super_admin` only |

#### Users Module
| Method | Endpoint | Auth |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/users` | `super_admin` only |
| `POST` | `/users` | `super_admin` only |
| `DELETE` | `/users/:id` | `super_admin` only |
| `PUT` | `/users/:id/bunk-access` | `super_admin` only |

#### Accounts Module
| Method | Endpoint | Auth |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/accounts?bunkId=` | Filtered by bunk access |
| `POST` | `/accounts` | Any authenticated user |
| `PUT` | `/accounts/:id` | Any authenticated user |
| `DELETE` | `/accounts/:id` | Any (with child-check) |

#### Vouchers Module
| Method | Endpoint | Auth |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/vouchers?bunkId=&date=` | Filtered by bunk + date |
| `POST` | `/vouchers` | Any authenticated user |
| `PUT` | `/vouchers/:id` | Any authenticated user |
| `DELETE` | `/vouchers/:id` | Any authenticated user |

#### Reminders Module
| Method | Endpoint | Auth |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/reminders` | Any authenticated user |
| `POST` | `/reminders` | Any authenticated user |
| `PUT` | `/reminders/:id` | Any authenticated user |
| `DELETE` | `/reminders/:id` | Any authenticated user |

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated вЂ” Backend Compilation
```bash
cd apps/backend
npm run build
```
Must compile with zero errors.

### Automated вЂ” NestJS Start
```bash
cd apps/backend
npm run start:dev
```
Server must start on port `3000` without crashes.

### Manual вЂ” API Testing
You can test the following endpoints manually using a browser or Postman:

1. **Login**: `POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login` with `{"username":"admin","password":"password123"}` в†’ should return a JWT token
2. **Get Bunks**: `GET http://localhost:3000/bunks` with `Authorization: Bearer <token>` в†’ should return the list of fuel stations
3. **Create Account**: `POST http://localhost:3000/accounts` with account data в†’ should persist to the database
4. **Get Vouchers**: `GET http://localhost:3000/vouchers?bunkId=<id>&date=2025-02-25` в†’ should return vouchers for that bunk/date

### Manual вЂ” Frontend Still Works
```bash
cd apps/frontend
npm run dev
```
Frontend should still run on `http://localhost:5173` without issues.
